13/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- About 300 employees of military plants in central BiH staged protests in front of the defence ministry in Sarajevo on Thursday (12 June).
They criticised government policy in the sector and demanded back pay.
The protestors also asked the government to improve health care services and other state benefits.
Union officials warned that similar protests might start in other sectors of the economy.
(Dnevni List - 13/06/03;
BiH TV - 12/06/03)
